1
00:00:05,980 --> 00:00:08,090
[All of Her]

2
00:00:08,110 --> 00:00:10,190
[Episode 2]

3
00:00:17,310 --> 00:00:17,840
Sister-in-law.

4
00:00:18,230 --> 00:00:19,120
Are you all right?

5
00:00:21,790 --> 00:00:24,850
[Elder brother, Chu Zejia;
Has been living abroad for years.]

6
00:00:24,870 --> 00:00:26,150
Ze'an, say hi.

7
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:31,230
(He's Zejia's younger brother,)

8
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:32,520
(Ze'an.)

9
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:36,270
Thank you.

10
00:00:36,910 --> 00:00:38,400
Second brother, you're back.

11
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:39,950
Excuse me.

12
00:00:40,470 --> 00:00:42,310
I'd like to request
all the reporters to leave.

13
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:43,560
[Chu Ze'an]
Thank you for your cooperation.

14
00:00:43,560 --> 00:00:45,950
[CFO of Anshi Group,
second son of the Chu family]

15
00:00:48,110 --> 00:00:48,720
Ze'an.

16
00:00:49,470 --> 00:00:50,400
Welcome back.

17
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:55,360
Your face

18
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:57,080
doesn't seem welcoming, though.

19
00:00:58,680 --> 00:00:59,840
Or should I say,

20
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,470
you don't welcome

21
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:03,880
this similar face like my brother's?

22
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:08,080
Zejia has gone,

23
00:01:08,950 --> 00:01:10,040
you're his only younger brother...

24
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:11,360
His body hasn't been found yet.

25
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,310
How are you so sure of that?

26
00:01:13,910 --> 00:01:14,590
Why?

27
00:01:15,190 --> 00:01:16,120
Can't wait to marry another guy?

28
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:16,800
Definitely.

29
00:01:17,040 --> 00:01:17,800
You're heartless.

30
00:01:17,910 --> 00:01:18,270
Xin.

31
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:21,190
Stop beating around the bush,
if you will.

32
00:01:28,610 --> 00:01:31,350
[Death Certificate]

33
00:01:32,310 --> 00:01:33,120
What do you mean?

34
00:01:33,630 --> 00:01:34,760
It means

35
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:37,000
that I disagree
with the death declaration.

36
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,360
No!

37
00:01:40,910 --> 00:01:41,720
Ze'an.

38
00:01:42,270 --> 00:01:43,360
You better

39
00:01:44,230 --> 00:01:45,910
stay out of this.

40
00:01:49,550 --> 00:01:50,080
What if I don't?

41
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,310
Are you going to make me disappear, too?

42
00:01:52,870 --> 00:01:53,630
What are you talking about?

43
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:54,230
Cheng.

44
00:01:54,550 --> 00:01:55,480
Leave it.

45
00:02:03,230 --> 00:02:04,510
You've been waiting a long time

46
00:02:04,870 --> 00:02:05,800
for this day, haven't you?

47
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,800
Citizens who disappear in an accident

48
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:13,030
for up to two years
could be declared legally dead.

49
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,030
The maximum period is four years.

50
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:16,240
If my brother dies,

51
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,670
naturally, his shares will become yours.

52
00:02:19,550 --> 00:02:21,440
Together with the shares you obtained
from other shareholders,

53
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:23,830
all of those actually make you
the largest shareholder.

54
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,670
But sorry,

55
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:28,670
my brother's shares

56
00:02:29,110 --> 00:02:31,320
are half held on my behalf.

57
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:33,110
So don't you put your eyes

58
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:35,440
on my shares.

59
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:43,270
Please look out for me

60
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,470
in the future.

61
00:02:45,630 --> 00:02:46,160
I'll take the bouquet.

62
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:48,470
Let's go.

63
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:58,000
You're allergic to lilies.

64
00:02:58,670 --> 00:02:59,440
He did this on purpose.

65
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,160
I'll go and meet the reporters.

66
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:18,720
(Why did Chu Ze'an return now?)

67
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:20,600
(This won't do.)

68
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,520
(I must find a way)

69
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,720
(to enter the file room)

70
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,270
(and find out the truth
of my parent's embezzlement case.)

71
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,360
Chu Ze'an suddenly came back.

72
00:04:07,670 --> 00:04:08,550
Look into it thoroughly.

73
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,030
Also,

74
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:11,720
arrange a meal

75
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:13,880
with the three shareholders tomorrow.

76
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,640
(If anything happens to me today,)

77
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:19,320
(you must pretend
you're clueless about it.)

78
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:21,000
(Promise me, and trust me)

79
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,480
(that I'll return to you
safe and sound.)

80
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:35,880
(Where am I?)

81
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:31,720
You...

82
00:06:33,110 --> 00:06:36,540
♪Waiting for the wilted flower
to finally fall silent♪

83
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:40,350
♪Waiting for the time
divides the sunset glow♪

84
00:06:40,710 --> 00:06:43,300
♪He stalks my mind and memories♪

85
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:44,760
I saved your life.

86
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:47,350
Is this how you treat your savior?

87
00:06:48,830 --> 00:06:50,640
I won't thank someone

88
00:06:51,230 --> 00:06:53,040
who pins me against the wall.

89
00:06:54,230 --> 00:06:55,000
It's fine.

90
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,480
I don't mind.

91
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,270
What are you up to?

92
00:06:59,610 --> 00:07:00,650
♪Tears are speaking♪

93
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:02,600
I want you to leave Anshi Group,

94
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:07,920
and reclaim everything
that belongs to my brother.

95
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:20,550
I booked you a flight to Cyprus.

96
00:07:21,070 --> 00:07:22,510
Everything has been arranged over there.

97
00:07:23,790 --> 00:07:25,760
You'll receive dividends every year

98
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,200
without missing a single cent.

99
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,440
Why did you take me here?

100
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:32,040
What do you want?

101
00:07:32,350 --> 00:07:33,440
So many questions.

102
00:07:34,350 --> 00:07:35,640
Which one should I answer first?

103
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:42,720
Are you in a hurry?

104
00:07:46,510 --> 00:07:48,790
That person dares
to gas you in the office.

105
00:07:49,110 --> 00:07:50,760
It means they are ready for anything.

106
00:07:52,110 --> 00:07:53,230
I might save you this time,

107
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,600
but you won't be so lucky next time.

108
00:07:57,350 --> 00:07:58,880
You're not scared at all, huh?

109
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:02,230
That needn't concern you.

110
00:08:15,270 --> 00:08:16,640
I'm so sorry.

111
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:18,440
I'm late.

112
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,230
It's rude if I come empty-handed.

113
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,550
So I brought you some little gifts.

114
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:23,830
Mr. Zhang.

115
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:26,270
You must've spent a lot
on over ten villas

116
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,440
you own in Gold City, right?

117
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:30,950
Ms. Yan, what's this?

118
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:34,960
I hope you like it.

119
00:08:39,910 --> 00:08:40,840
I heard

120
00:08:41,110 --> 00:08:43,320
that your son is doing quite well
in his studies overseas.

121
00:08:43,550 --> 00:08:45,320
He's very into firearms.

122
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:48,080
But it seems that firearms are illegal

123
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,000
in the place he stays.

124
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:01,590
For the future of Anshi Group,

125
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:02,960
I'd like to thank you.

126
00:09:04,590 --> 00:09:07,030
May our collaboration benefit us.

127
00:09:11,790 --> 00:09:13,110
I've already warned her.

128
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,520
She should

129
00:09:14,790 --> 00:09:15,910
keep her actions in check.

130
00:09:29,030 --> 00:09:30,030
It seems that you're not going

131
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:31,640
to accept my offer.

132
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:35,280
Do you really mean to help me?

133
00:09:43,710 --> 00:09:44,350
Of course.

134
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:49,400
How about

135
00:09:50,350 --> 00:09:52,110
you transfer your shares to me?

136
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,880
I ask you to leave
because I want to help you.

137
00:09:55,110 --> 00:09:56,000
Do you understand?

138
00:09:59,590 --> 00:10:00,960
If you had stayed in that break room

139
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:01,880
any longer that day,

140
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:03,150
the gas could've killed you.

141
00:10:03,710 --> 00:10:04,670
If I die,

142
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:07,080
the shares will return
to the Chu family.

143
00:10:07,230 --> 00:10:08,710
Why do you want me to leave?

144
00:10:09,030 --> 00:10:09,590
Because...

145
00:10:13,670 --> 00:10:14,710
I'm a good guy.

146
00:10:29,350 --> 00:10:31,710
(Why do I feel something familiar
about you?)

147
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,760
(Who are you?)

148
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:41,710
Answer me.

149
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:44,350
Why do you want me to leave?

150
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:47,230
I told you.

151
00:10:47,710 --> 00:10:48,910
Because I'm a good guy.

152
00:10:49,350 --> 00:10:50,080
Or maybe

153
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:52,520
you don't believe there are good people
in this world?

154
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:58,080
♪Promises are answering his lies♪

155
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:01,870
♪I'm just a walker-on
in this tear-jerker♪

156
00:11:02,140 --> 00:11:05,670
♪Tick, tock, tick, tock♪

157
00:11:05,750 --> 00:11:09,030
♪Tears are speaking♪

158
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:12,440
Zhen.

159
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:14,110
Humans

160
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,550
don't hold up under temptation.

161
00:11:16,110 --> 00:11:18,150
Zejia also used the same aftershave.

162
00:11:18,180 --> 00:11:20,910
♪Love me, will you? Quiet, silly♪

163
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:21,910
He recommended this to me.

164
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,350
Quite nice.

165
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:27,350
Change it.

166
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,230
The smell is too strong.

167
00:11:30,030 --> 00:11:30,640
Zhen.

168
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,030
Don't be so aggressive.

169
00:11:34,790 --> 00:11:35,790
There aren't many good guys
in this world

170
00:11:36,150 --> 00:11:37,790
like me.

171
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:39,000
I don't care.

172
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:43,440
I have nothing much to lose, anyway.

173
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:47,710
♪I stay under the limp spring blossom♪

174
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:51,290
♪Trimming off all the mess♪

175
00:11:51,410 --> 00:11:58,050
♪So happiness may bloom flawlessly♪

176
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:04,960
(You'll be in great trouble)

177
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:07,080
(if you don't stop, you know?)

178
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:14,160
♪Promises are answering his lies♪

179
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:18,060
♪I'm just a walker-on
in this tear-jerker♪

180
00:12:18,420 --> 00:12:21,860
♪Tick, tock, tick, tock♪

181
00:12:22,030 --> 00:12:24,920
♪Tears are speaking♪

182
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:29,380
♪Mist blinds his eyes
from seeing rose graffiti♪

183
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:33,260
♪The dialogue sounds hoarse,
I can only hide my words within♪

184
00:12:33,330 --> 00:12:37,060
♪Love me, will you? Quiet, silly♪

185
00:12:37,350 --> 00:12:40,080
♪Or just let it go?♪

186
00:12:40,950 --> 00:12:44,550
♪My youth is like burning snowflakes♪

187
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:48,410
♪Your castle is fended♪

188
00:12:48,650 --> 00:12:52,310
♪Let the heavy downpour
awaken the summer♪

189
00:12:52,580 --> 00:12:55,750
♪I turn away from glamor♪

190
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:59,920
♪Your garden is sown with fairy tales♪

191
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:03,740
♪I stay under the limp spring blossom♪

192
00:13:04,180 --> 00:13:07,530
♪Trimming off all the mess♪

193
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:12,480
♪So happiness may bloom flawlessly♪

194
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,760
[Humans tend to evade the most
fundamental problem instinctively]

195
00:13:14,770 --> 00:13:17,030
[until they have to face it.
Seicho Matsumoto]
